tions. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Here are the best free WordPress travel booking plugins: </h3>\n\n\n\n<p>In this article, I&#8217;ve listed top downloaded WordPress travel booking plugins. This list contains only the best travel booking plugins. These plugins will help you to create your travel websites that manage travel booking, payment system, pricing travel package, hotel booking and many more. Following are the list of best free WordPress travel booking plugins: </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>WP Travel Engine</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/WordPress-Travel-Booking-Plugin-Screen_Shot-1024x478.png\" alt=\"WordPress-Travel-Booking-Plugin-Screen_Shot.png\" class=\"wp-image-7684\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/WordPress-Travel-Booking-Plugin-Screen_Shot-1024x478.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/WordPress-Travel-Booking-Plugin-Screen_Shot-300x140.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/WordPress-Travel-Booking-Plugin-Screen_Shot-768x358.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/WordPress-Travel-Booking-Plugin-Screen_Shot.png 1282w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>WP Travel Engine is one of the best free WordPress travel booking plugins that allows you to create travel &amp; tour packages. The travel &amp; tour packages are for travel agencies and operator agencies. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>This plugin is bound to have a complete management system for tour &amp; travel packages. It also includes lots of realistic and useful features for travel &amp; tour.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Using this plugin you can easily create your tour &amp; travel booking website within less than five minutes. It is a smart travel booking plugin so, do not worry about the payment process, booking details, travel packages, etc. You will be able to customize all the features easily. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Features</h3>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Unlimited Travel Packages</li><li>Activities &amp; Trip Types Pages</li><li>Unlimited Trip Facts</li><li>Smart Travel Booking Process</li><li>Payment Processing</li><li>Change Currency</li><li>Destination Page</li><li>Unlimited Facts</li><li>Email Notification</li><li>Enquiry Form</li><li>Itinerary Builder</li><li>Translation Ready</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"button-block\">\n<a class=\"btn-general\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-travel-engine/\" target=\"_blank\">Details/Downloads WP Travel Engine</a>\n\n<a class=\"btn-general get-hosting\" rel=\"dofollow noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/best-wordpress-hosting-compared/\" target=\"_blank\">Get Hosting</a>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<h2>Travelpayouts</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Travelpayouts-Screen_Shot-1024x469.png\" alt=\"Travelpayouts-Screen_Shot.png\" class=\"wp-image-7685\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Travelpayouts-Screen_Shot-1024x469.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Travelpayouts-Screen_Shot-300x138.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Travelpayouts-Screen_Shot-768x352.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Travelpayouts-Screen_Shot.png 1300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Travelpayout is a suitable plugin for helping your customers or visitors to find best offering price according to their travel needs. It helps in comparing the price of the cheapest hotels and flights.  </p>\n\n\n\n<p>It is one of the best free WordPress travel booking plugins that add value to your website and increases your source of income. This plugin has multiple payment options, multiple hotel widgets, 11 different tables and many more features. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>It is the best solution for travel &amp; tour agencies, travel bloggers and websites relating to tour &amp; travel.  This plugin makes your user happy and brings you a steady profit income. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3> Features </h3>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>11 customizable tables with flight information</li><li>Easy to use &amp; customize</li><li>Responsive</li><li>Multiple Payment Options</li><li>2 customizable tables with hotel prices and info</li><li>Translation Ready</li><li>Search Forms</li><li>Low-cost flights and hotels Map</li><li>Low prices Calendar</li><li>Responsive Design</li><li>Hotel Widget</li><li>Popular flight destinations Widget </li></ul>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"button-block\">\n<a class=\"btn-general\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/travelpayouts/\" target=\"_blank\">Details/Downloads Travelpayouts</a>\n\n<a class=\"btn-general get-hosting\" rel=\"dofollow noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/best-wordpress-hosting-compared/\" target=\"_blank\">Get Hosting</a>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<h2>WP Travel</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/WP-Travel-Screen_Shot-1024x463.png\" alt=\"WP-Travel-Screen_Shot.png\" class=\"wp-image-7686\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/WP-Travel-Screen_Shot-1024x463.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/WP-Travel-Screen_Shot-300x136.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/WP-Travel-Screen_Shot-768x347.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/WP-Travel-Screen_Shot.png 1292w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>WP travel is one of the powerful and best free WordPress travel booking plugins that is used to make travel websites. With this plugin, you will be able to create a travel &amp; tour websites within a minute. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Everything in this plugin can be easily customizable such as travel package plans for flight, booking hotels, inserting add-ons, payment methods, etc. and many more. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>This powerful plugin is scalable and easiest tour &amp; travel management plugin for best agency WordPress themes. Moreover, it handles bookings, travelling schedules, payments, travel reports, email notification etc. that needs to be in your travel &amp; tour website. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3> Features </h3>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Tour Filters &amp; Tour Extra</li><li>Painless Booking System</li><li>Unlimited Tour Packages</li><li>Multiple Payment Options</li><li>Full Data Reporting</li><li>Tax Options</li><li>User Dashboard</li><li>Email Notification</li><li>Customizable Tabs</li><li>Multiple Pricing and Multiple dates</li><li>Trip Facts</li><li>Rating and Review</li><li>Map &amp; Coupon</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"button-block\">\n<a class=\"btn-general\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-travel/\" target=\"_blank\">Details/Downloads WP Travel</a>\n\n<a class=\"btn-general get-hosting\" rel=\"dofollow noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/best-wordpress-hosting-compared/\" target=\"_blank\">Get Hosting</a>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<h2>Travel Booking Toolkit</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Travel-Booking-Toolkit-Screen_Shot-1024x478.png\" alt=\"Travel-Booking-Toolkit-Screen_Shot.png\" class=\"wp-image-7687\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Travel-Booking-Toolkit-Screen_Shot-1024x478.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Travel-Booking-Toolkit-Screen_Shot-300x140.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Travel-Booking-Toolkit-Screen_Shot-768x358.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Travel-Booking-Toolkit-Screen_Shot.png 1278w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Travel Booking Toolkit is one of the best free WordPress travel booking plugins that add additional functionality in your travel &amp; tour website. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>It is for creating travel &amp; tour website that helps your visitors/customers for booking travel, creating suitable travel packages, maintain payment mechanism, etc.  With this plugin, you will be able to create your travel website in less than five minutes. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>This plugin adds additional functionality to your admin area, customizer section and widgets section. It is for boosting your website overall performance and brings you better results. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3> Features </h3>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Easy to Customize</li><li>Tour Filters &amp; Tour Extra</li><li>Unlimited Tour Packages</li><li>Painless Booking System</li><li>Email Notification</li><li>Multiple Payment Options</li><li>Full Data Reporting</li><li>User Dashboard</li><li>Customizable Tabs</li><li>Trip Facts</li><li>Rating and Review</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"button-block\">\n<a class=\"btn-general\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/travel-booking-toolkit/\" target=\"_blank\">Details/Downloads Travel Booking Toolkit</a>\n\n<a class=\"btn-general get-hosting\" rel=\"dofollow noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/best-wordpress-hosting-compared/\" target=\"_blank\">Get Hosting</a>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<h2>WP Ride Booking</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/WP-Ride-Booking-Screen_Shot-1024x474.png\" alt=\"WP-Ride-Booking-Screen_Shot.png\" class=\"wp-image-7688\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/WP-Ride-Booking-Screen_Shot-1024x474.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/WP-Ride-Booking-Screen_Shot-300x139.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/WP-Ride-Booking-Screen_Shot-768x356.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/WP-Ride-Booking-Screen_Shot.png 1278w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>WP Ride Booking is a powerful travel plugin that is for travel booking purpose. In particular, it is for travel-related websites such as for booking a taxi, bus, couriers and caps. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>It is suitable for travel agencies that focus on providing transportation facilities. This plugin calculates the distance travelled as well as calculating rate as per kilometre. It is easy to use also. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>This WP Ride Booking is one of the best free WordPress travel booking plugins for transportation travel agencies. It directly accepts payments from customers PayPal account. </p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"button-block\">\n<a class=\"btn-general\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-ride-booking/\" target=\"_blank\">Details/Downloads WP Ride Booking</a>\n\n<a class=\"btn-general get-hosting\" rel=\"dofollow noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/best-wordpress-hosting-compared/\" target=\"_blank\">Get Hosting</a>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The overall operation of your travel website totally depends on you. I hope these plugins helped you to create genuine travel &amp; tour websites. Keep in mind these plugins will only extend the travel related functionality that your travel website actually needs. The rest management travel process remains on you. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>That being said, this is the end of the list of best free WordPress travel booking plugins. If you want to comment or recommend other travel booking plugin then leave them in the comment section below. </p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/best-free-wordpress-travel-booking-plugins/\">4+ Best Free WordPress Travel booking Plugins</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://themebeez.com/blog\">Themebeez Blog</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:75:\"https://themebeez.com/blog/best-free-wordpress-travel-booking-plugins/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:82:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"20+ Tips To Improve WordPress Security (2020 Guide)\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:46:\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wordpress-security/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wordpress-security/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 15 Apr 2020 13:40:35 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:18:\"WordPress Tutorial\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"Secure\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Security\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Wp security\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:34:\"https://themebeez.com/blog/?p=7511\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:349:\"<p>WordPress security is a growing concern growth of WordPress popularity with the Currently, WordPress the...</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wordpress-security/\">20+ Tips To Improve WordPress Security (2020 Guide)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://themebeez.com/blog\">Themebeez Blog</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"Editorial staff\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27787:\"\n<p>WordPress security is a growing concern growth of WordPress popularity with the Currently, WordPress the most commonly used Content Management System (CMS) platform and it powers 35% of websites on the internet. Its popularity has made it the most common target for hacking. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>100% security is to myth for us. Not only WordPress, but other web platforms also cannot provide us with 100% security. It means every platform has vulnerabilities and they can be hacked. But it does not mean that we cannot strengthen our security. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here, I have shared some of the security tips that can strengthen your WordPress security. It will also cover your website vulnerabilities and prevent your website from being hacked. </p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<h2><strong>Basic WordPress Security Tips</strong> </h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Basic WordPress security tips are related to simple and easy tips that do not require coding. These tips are simple but effective. They are as follows: </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Change Initial &#8220;Admin&#8221; Administrator Username to other Username</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-Screen_Shot-1024x543.png\" alt=\"WPS-Screen_Shot.png\" class=\"wp-image-7929\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-Screen_Shot-1024x543.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-Screen_Shot-300x159.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-Screen_Shot-768x407.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-Screen_Shot.png 1487w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Most of us enter our Administrator Username as &#8220;Admin&#8221; which is very much common in practice. Thus that creates an opening for hackers. They just have to figure out the password of your dashboard. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>What you can do is, you have to change your administrator username &#8220;admin&#8221; into other names with administration privileges. You can also place capital letters in that username. It is basic but effective way of keeping your WordPress security tight.  Be sure to change the username form blog posts and pages also. </p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<h3>Set Strong Password </h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-02-Screen_Shot-1024x590.png\" alt=\"WPS 02 Screen_Shot\" class=\"wp-image-7930\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-02-Screen_Shot-1024x590.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-02-Screen_Shot-300x173.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-02-Screen_Shot-768x443.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-02-Screen_Shot.png 1282w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Weak WordPress security password creates vulnerability in your website. We know a weak password has a higher possibility of being hacked than strong ones. We set a weak password cause it will be easy for us to remember. But weak password has a pattern such as <strong>123456, 696969, 123456789, 123123, 111111, 7777777, 0000000,</strong> or other numbers pattern or simple words like <strong>baseball, password, shadow, dragon, batman, killer, hunter, superman, Michael,</strong> etc. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>So, how to set Strong Password?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To set a strong password </p>\n\n\n\n<p>First, you must have to make your WordPress security password lengthy (at least 15 characters) and hard to guess. Meaning it must be unique. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Second, use alphabet, numbers and symbols. (Mixing)</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Note: Do not use your pet name, date of birth or any of your personal information in your password. </p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<h3> Pick trustworthy hosting providers</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-03-Screen_Shot-1024x634.png\" alt=\"WPS 03 Screen_Shot\" class=\"wp-image-7931\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-03-Screen_Shot-1024x634.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-03-Screen_Shot-300x186.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-03-Screen_Shot-768x475.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-03-Screen_Shot.png 1264w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>To break through your website first hackers must pass through your hosting providers. Weak hosting companies cannot provide you with strong WordPress security features. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Therefore, you must pick the right hosting company for your website. Right hosting companies can provide you with better security features with 24/7 security monitoring. Choose those hosting providers that support firewall, the latest version of MySQL, PHP, and Apache. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>There are many hosting companies with DDOS prevention measures. It will be better if your hosting companies scan malware regularly and perform daily backups. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you do not know which hosting company is better for security then check out <a aria-label=\"BEST MANAGED WORDPRESS HOSTING PROVIDERS (opens in a new tab)\" class=\"rank-math-link rank-math-link\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/best-managed-wordpress-hosting-provider/\" target=\"_blank\">Best managed WordPress hosting providers.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<h3>Keep your WordPress Updated</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Updates-Screen_Shot.jpg\" alt=\"Updates Screen_Shot.jpg\" class=\"wp-image-7410\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Updates-Screen_Shot.jpg 960w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Updates-Screen_Shot-300x174.jpg 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Updates-Screen_Shot-768x446.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Updating WordPress dashboard is necessary for WordPress security purpose. According to the data of 2020,  out of 4000 known vulnerabilities, 31.5% of WordPress websites are hacked from core WordPress. It means if WordPress dashboard is not updated and you are still using an older version then your WordPress website will be easily hacked. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>For WordPress security purpose, you have to update your WordPress dashboard. It is not only precaution measure but it also helps to maintain your website. Don&#8217;t be afraid of WordPress update just cope with it. If you cope with the update your website design will not be affected. </p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<h3>Keep themes and plugins Updated </h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-04-Screen_Shot.Png-1024x576.png\" alt=\"WPS 04 Screen_Shot.Png\" class=\"wp-image-7932\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-04-Screen_Shot.Png-1024x576.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-04-Screen_Shot.Png-300x169.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-04-Screen_Shot.Png-768x432.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-04-Screen_Shot.Png-400x226.png 400w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-04-Screen_Shot.Png.png 1280w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Themes and plugins must be updated in time. The update refers to new additional features and fixes of old errors. Updates are done not only to provide new features to users but also to fix bugs and problems created by new updates of WordPress. It also helps to avoid bugs, potential WordPress security risks, and vulnerabilities. Outdated plugins and themes are a major weakness to WordPress websites. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Therefore update your themes and plugins in time. Do not be afraid of update of themes and plugins. Just contact to the developer if any problem arises. They will help you to fix the error and as well as it will help the developer if there are any problems in there theme and plugins. </p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<h3>Download themes and plugins from authentic sources only </h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-05-Screen_Shot-1024x835.png\" alt=\"WPS 05 Screen_Shot\" class=\"wp-image-7933\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-05-Screen_Shot-1024x835.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-05-Screen_Shot-300x245.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-05-Screen_Shot-768x627.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-05-Screen_Shot-1536x1253.png 1536w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-05-Screen_Shot.png 1916w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Do not download themes and plugins from unknown websites. The downloaded themes and plugins may be faked or nulled. According to data 2020, out of 4000 WordPress websites, 54 % are hacked using facked plugins and 14.5% are hacked using fake WordPress themes. I will explain below how nulled themes will destroy your website security. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Therefore download themes that are found in <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/\" target=\"_blank\" aria-label=\"WordPress.org (opens in a new tab)\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\" class=\"rank-math-link\">WordPress.org</a> search results or you can go to the link to the real website of developers or you can download themes from well-known sources. </p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<h3>Install firewall on Your Computer</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-06-Screen_Shot.Png-1024x683.png\" alt=\"WPS 06 Screen_Shot.Png\" class=\"wp-image-7934\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-06-Screen_Shot.Png-1024x683.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-06-Screen_Shot.Png-300x200.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-06-Screen_Shot.Png-768x512.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-06-Screen_Shot.Png-1536x1024.png 1536w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-06-Screen_Shot.Png.png 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Your computer must be free from any kinds of potential threats of being hacked. Installing firewall on your computer helps protects your computer from online threats and other suspicious activities that attempt to connect with your computer. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>If your computer is safe from hackers then your website will be also safe from those hackers who try to connect a link to your computer.</p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<h3>Use WordPress Security Plugins</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>WordPress security plugins are created to protect WordPress dashboard and websites secure from potential hacking and threats. They build an extra defending wall for hackers. They identify and blocks any malicious or malware traffics. Security plugins reduce security risks. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Therefore use WordPress security plugins build an additional wall for hackers. You can use security plugins like All in One WP Security &amp; Firewall, Wordfence,  Plugin Security, etc. </p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<h3>Enable Security scans</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-07-Screen_Shot-1-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"WPS 07 Screen_Shot (1)\" class=\"wp-image-7935\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-07-Screen_Shot-1-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-07-Screen_Shot-1-300x200.jpg 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-07-Screen_Shot-1-768x512.jpg 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-07-Screen_Shot-1-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-07-Screen_Shot-1.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Enable security scans of your security plugins. Security scanning is needed for your website.  Although it takes time you have to scan through your website as a precaution. Enabling security scans will scan your whole websites to make sure there are not any suspicious activities going on. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>These security scans will work as anti-virus on your websites that removes all the suspicious activities and notify you immediately. Enable security scans when you need scans. The shorter scanning time period the more it will be effective. I recommend at least monthly. If you think your hosting company and has vulnerabilities then it will be better to do weekly or daily. </p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<h3>Don&#8217;t use nulled themes and plugins</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/avoid-nulled-wordpress-themes-and-plugins-featured-image.jpg\" alt=\"avoid nulled themes and plugins\" class=\"wp-image-6532\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/avoid-nulled-wordpress-themes-and-plugins-featured-image.jpg 945w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/avoid-nulled-wordpress-themes-and-plugins-featured-image-300x170.jpg 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/avoid-nulled-wordpress-themes-and-plugins-featured-image-768x435.jpg 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/avoid-nulled-wordpress-themes-and-plugins-featured-image-400x226.jpg 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 945px) 100vw, 945px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>If you download themes form unknown and unauthentic websites without having knowledge is considerable but by knowing if you are using nulled WordPress themes and plugins then you must be looking for trouble. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Nulled WordPress and plugins are those themes and plugins that are a modified version of pro or premium WordPress themes and plugins (No copyright). They are uploaded in online for people to use it for free. But remember many of the nulled themes contains malware that can destroy your entire website.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In short, do not use nulled WordPress themes and plugins. Many of them contains malware infections and destroy your websites. For more learn it from  <a aria-label=\"WHY YOU SHOULD AVOID NULLED WORDPRESS THEMES &amp; PLUGINS (opens in a new tab)\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/nulled-wordpress-themes-plugins/\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"rank-math-link\">Why you should avoid nulled WordPress themes &amp; plugins.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<h3>Ensure regular backups</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-08-Screen_Shot-2-1024x553.jpg\" alt=\"WPS 08 Screen_Shot (2)\" class=\"wp-image-7937\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-08-Screen_Shot-2-1024x553.jpg 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-08-Screen_Shot-2-300x162.jpg 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-08-Screen_Shot-2-768x415.jpg 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-08-Screen_Shot-2-1536x830.jpg 1536w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-08-Screen_Shot-2.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Make sure you have backup or copy of your website data. If anything goes wrong with your website you can still able to build your website like before. It is the best precaution for you. You can easily restore your website. If you do not have then start it right now. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>There are lots of plugins that will help you to recover your website in WordPress.org, such as UpdraftPlus, Backup WordPress, etc. </p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<h3>Monitor login History </h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Your login history can tell a lot about your activities in your dashboard and website. Keep tracking your login and monitor all your activities yourself and look if there are any suspicious activities. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>It is simple but effective. If you found any irregular time of login then change your password and username. It&#8217;s auditing your website login history. </p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<h2><strong>Technical Security Tips</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Technical security tips refer to the default settings of WordPress dashboard. In some case, you need codes and deep knowledge of those settings.  These tips are not hard to deal with. But takes your little time and effort. It is better to know and it provides additional security of your websites. They are as follows: </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Always use two authentication factor for login</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-09-Screen_Shot.Png-1024x674.jpg\" alt=\"WPS 09 Screen_Shot.Png\" class=\"wp-image-7938\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-09-Screen_Shot.Png-1024x674.jpg 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-09-Screen_Shot.Png-300x197.jpg 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-09-Screen_Shot.Png-768x505.jpg 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-09-Screen_Shot.Png-1536x1010.jpg 1536w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-09-Screen_Shot.Png.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You must use two authentication factor for login. Even though your password is strong, they might get hacked by hackers. Therefore having two authentication factors for login will help you prevent from hackers by establishing a verification process while login. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>For two factor authentication, you must download plugins. Then by installing the plugin, you can connect it to your email address. While login, you have to enter the code that is in your email address. </p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<h3>Be sure to hide your WordPress update version number</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>You must hide your WordPress version number. Hackers who are looking for an opportunity can see your WordPress version number by inspecting source codes. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can install plugins to hide your WordPress version number or you can add codes in your dashboard. </p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<h3>Automatically Logout idle users</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-10-Screen_Shot-1024x580.png\" alt=\"WPS-10-Screen_Shot.png\" class=\"wp-image-7940\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-10-Screen_Shot-1024x580.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-10-Screen_Shot-300x170.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-10-Screen_Shot-768x435.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-10-Screen_Shot-400x226.png 400w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-10-Screen_Shot.png 1411w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>If you have a habit of leaving your user Id and password logged in your browser then that can create a massive problem. It makes easy for anyone to go through your dashboard and change the existing settings. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Either you have to logout your Id manually or you have to install a plugin in your dashboard that will automatically log out your Id after a certain time period. </p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<h3>Disable PHP Error Reports</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Php error reports will help you to find an error on your website. It displays the error in your screen. But it is not a good idea cause it exposes your server path to potential threats and dangers. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Therefore you have to disable Php reports. Copy the code </p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">error_reporting(0) \n@ini_set(\'display_errors\', 0);&nbsp; </pre>\n\n\n\n<p>Paste this above code somewhere in your wp-config.php file.</p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<h3>Use SSL and HTTPS</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>HTTPS refers to the Hypertext Transfer Protocol Secure and SSL refers to Secure Socket Layers.  Using HTTPS and SSL allows your visitors to have a secure connection to your website. The information between your websites and visitor browser will be encrypted. Additionally, it also provides benefits in your Google search engine. </p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<h3>Customize your login URL</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>In WordPress, we find our login URL as yoursitename.com/wp-admin or yoursitename.com/ wp-login.php. It is the default of WordPress and many of the hackers take advantage of this case. They have access to your login page. Then they start to crack your password to get the login. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Hence we have to change our login URL. You can find security plugins for changing your website login URL. </p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<h3>Diable your login hints</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>While login you may enter wrong password or username or the password is changed or older password or password has been changed etc. Your login page may give you a hint about your username and password. This makes an opportunity for hackers. It makes their work easier to crack your username and password. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Thus you should disable your login hints. To disable it, insert it in the functions.php file</p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">function no_wordpress_errors(){\n\n   <code>return \'Access Denied\';</code>\n}\nadd_filter( \'login_errors\', \'no_wordpress_errors\' );</pre>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<h3>Disable trackbacks</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Go to your dashboard&gt;Settings&gt;Dicussion and unchecked the &#8221; pingbacks and trackbacks &#8221; option. It&#8217;s for newcomers. Hackers can use trackbacks to hack other websites. It is related to DDoS attacks. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>It is best for new websites or newcomers to have trackbacks disable although it provides some merits. </p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<h3>Protect your wp-config.php file</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Wp-config.php file is the core file of our WordPress. We put all our data on our wp-config.php file in the process of installing WordPress. The file is the root directory of our websites and it consists of important data about your website. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you secure the wp-config.php file by moving it to your other higher-level root directory, your core file is hard to access for hackers and they can not breach your website security. </p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<h3>Disable XML-RPC</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>XML-RPC helps to connect WordPress mobile applications and plugins. Using HTTP protocols, it passes data from a client device to a server device. It provides an opening for hackers to send commands to gain access to your website. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Hence disable XML-RPC. You can search plugins in WordPress.org to disable XML-RPC. Just enter disable XML-RPC. </p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<h3>Disable the WordPress theme and plugin editing</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>You may have other users who have access to your WordPress dashboard. They may change your theme and plugins or install other similar plugins and themes by removing the existing one. That can create lots of headache to us if someone changes our current themes and plugins. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you disable the editing of the WordPress theme and plugin in your dashboard then you can have much more control over your theme setting and plugin setting. Enter the following code at the end of your wp-config.php file. </p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">// Disable file edit \ndefine(\'DISALLOW_FILE_EDIT\', true);</pre>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<h3>Turnoff Directory Browsing </h3>\n\n\n\n<p>You should block the path of your directory files. Its where we keep our data or information about our website. If someone has got access inside your directory, they can leave malicious codes and start to hack your website. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>You have to add code at the bottom of your .htaccess file to turn off your directory browsing. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Limit Dashboard Accessibility</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-11-Screen_Shot-1024x458.png\" alt=\"WPS 11 Screen_Shot\" class=\"wp-image-7941\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-11-Screen_Shot-1024x458.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-11-Screen_Shot-300x134.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-11-Screen_Shot-768x343.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-11-Screen_Shot-1536x687.png 1536w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-11-Screen_Shot.png 1917w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Dashboard accessibility should be maintained. There may be multiple authors, contributors, editors, and users to access the dashboard. Being the administration you must maintain the accessibility of your dashboard and classify your user&#8217;s accessibility in such a way that you will have full control over your dashboard. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Note limiting dashboard accessibility provides full control to administration and the role of editors, contributors, authors and users are clearly defined. </p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<h3>Limit logins based on number of fail attempts</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-12-Screen_Shot-1024x560.png\" alt=\"WPS 12 Screen_Shot\" class=\"wp-image-7942\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-12-Screen_Shot-1024x560.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-12-Screen_Shot-300x164.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-12-Screen_Shot-768x420.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WPS-12-Screen_Shot.png 1468w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>If someone wants to log in and fails, again and again, provides an opening to attempt more for forceful login. It is not a good sign to login after so many attempts. Hackers will be benefited if you do not set a limitation on the number of failed attempts. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Therefore, you must set a limitation on the number of attempts or wrong password like Facebook, Gmail, etc. The wrong password is a trial and error approach for hackers so it is better to limit the attempt. </p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Even though you cannot have full 100% tight security, you can always reduce the percentage of getting hacked from hackers. If you follow the above WordPress security tips, your website will have fewer vulnerabilities that also reduces the chance of getting hacked. The security of your WordPress websites heavily depends on how you take precaution measures. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Besides those tips, you can change your password regularly, keeping your WordPress clean (remove unnecessary plugins or files), block hotlinks, use security plugins, changing and WordPress database table prefix.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can leave your comment and suggestion down below in comment section. </p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wordpress-security/\">20+ Tips To Improve WordPress Security (2020 Guide)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://themebeez.com/blog\">Themebeez Blog</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wordpress-security/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:82:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:68:\"Cream Magazine Version 2.0.0 (Optimized, Features &amp; Performance)\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:56:\"https://themebeez.com/blog/cream-magazine-version-2-0-0/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:65:\"https://themebeez.com/blog/cream-magazine-version-2-0-0/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 07 Apr 2020 15:16:57 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"News & Updates\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Cream Mag\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"Cream Magazine\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"Updates\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:34:\"https://themebeez.com/blog/?p=7728\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:377:\"<p>Cream Magazine has been an unexpected outcome for us, themebeez.com. We&#8217;ve had never expected that...</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/cream-magazine-version-2-0-0/\">Cream Magazine Version 2.0.0 (Optimized, Features &#038; Performance)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://themebeez.com/blog\">Themebeez Blog</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Themebeez editor\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:22652:\"\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://themebeez.com/themes/cream-magazine/\" target=\"_blank\" aria-label=\"Cream Magazine (opens in a new tab)\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"rank-math-link\">Cream Magazine</a></strong> has been an unexpected outcome for us, <a class=\"rank-math-link\" href=\"https://themebeez.com\">themebeez.com</a>. We&#8217;ve had never expected that it would be this theme that would be well-liked and loved by many people like you. To thank you for your love and support, we&#8217;ve released a major update of the theme.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Although we&#8217;ve released updates of Cream Magazine before, those updates were for either bug fixes or design fixes or the addition of minor functionalities or WordPress&#8217;s theme requirement updates.  Whereas, in this update, we&#8217;ve considered and did our best on the enhancement of the theme for better performance, user experience, customization options and many more.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large image-shadow\"><img src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/cream-magazine-update-2-is-here-1024x504.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-7764\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/cream-magazine-update-2-is-here-1024x504.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/cream-magazine-update-2-is-here-300x148.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/cream-magazine-update-2-is-here-768x378.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/cream-magazine-update-2-is-here-1536x755.png 1536w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/cream-magazine-update-2-is-here.png 1816w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /><figcaption>Cream Magazine version <strong>2.0.0</strong> is here 🥰🎉</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Let&#8217;s dig down about the changes that are made on Cream Magazine 2.0.0.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2><strong>Refined And Updated Design.</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>There were many issues that the older version of <strong>Bootstrap</strong> could not handle. So, we have updated the CSS framework, <strong>Bootstrap</strong>, to the latest version which not only helped to resolve those issues but manage elements more easily.</li><li>There are some changes to the design of some elements such as ticker news, categories meta, search form, etc.</li><li>And we have fixed spacing issues, typography issues, color issues, RTL issues, etc.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>Page Load Speed.</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Focusing on page load speed, we have made some changes to the built-in feature that used for lazy loading images. With the <strong>Lazy Load</strong> feature, without installing any third-party plugin, your page will still load fast. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let&#8217;s perform three different tests with Cream Magazine version 2.0.0.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large image-shadow\"><img src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/cream-magazine-update-2-speed-test-without-3rd-party-pulgin-1024x442.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-7776\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/cream-magazine-update-2-speed-test-without-3rd-party-pulgin-1024x442.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/cream-magazine-update-2-speed-test-without-3rd-party-pulgin-300x129.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/cream-magazine-update-2-speed-test-without-3rd-party-pulgin-768x331.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/cream-magazine-update-2-speed-test-without-3rd-party-pulgin.png 1358w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /><figcaption>Hosted in Amsterdam data center &amp; tested will full demo data. No, any optimizer plugin is used in this test</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Did you notice something? As the page was full of demo data &amp; images used in demo data were heavy. The size of a page during this test is <strong>9.09MB</strong> but still, the default lazy load functionality in Cream Magazine really helped to boost the page load speed dramatically fast.  </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The above tests was made with-out any 3rd party plugin &amp; optimizer. Since we had bloated our test with full demo data we though to re-test the same instance using a simple free optimizer plugin called <a aria-label=\"autooptimize  (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/autoptimize/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\" class=\"rank-math-link\">Auto Optimize</a> plugin. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here is the result below&#8230; 🧡</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large image-shadow\"><img src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/cream-magazine-update-2-page-speed-score-1024x409.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-7774\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/cream-magazine-update-2-page-speed-score-1024x409.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/cream-magazine-update-2-page-speed-score-300x120.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/cream-magazine-update-2-page-speed-score-768x307.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/cream-magazine-update-2-page-speed-score.png 1368w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /><figcaption>Hosted in Amsterdam data center &amp; tested will full demo data. Plugin used &#8220;AutoOptimize&#8221;</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>If you are wondering how other authors do a speed test for their themes &amp; claim <strong>1s</strong> load time we can help you to understand that test too. They either create a lightweight demo with very fewer demo data or they test their themes in a clean fresh WordPress installation. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you want the same way other authors do speed testing then fine here we go&#8230;. 😎.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large image-shadow\"><img src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/cream-magazine-update-2-speed-test-blank-cream-magazine-1024x552.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-7792\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/cream-magazine-update-2-speed-test-blank-cream-magazine-1024x552.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/cream-magazine-update-2-speed-test-blank-cream-magazine-300x162.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/cream-magazine-update-2-speed-test-blank-cream-magazine-768x414.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/cream-magazine-update-2-speed-test-blank-cream-magazine.png 1135w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /><figcaption>Blank Cream Magazine network load test using Chrome network tool</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Blank Cream Magazine loads just in <strong>754ms</strong>. We hope you are satisfied with the speed test results. We look forward to making it even faster in upcoming updates 👍</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Talking about the Lazy load feature that Cream Magazine has in default, it helps to load your website faster by loading the only images that comes to the visitor&#8217;s web browser viewport. To get this feature on your website, you&#8217;ll have to enable the image Lazy load option. Follow the instructions below to enable the option:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Navigate to <em>Appearance &gt; Customize &gt; Theme Customization &gt; Site Image</em>.</li><li>Enable the option <em>Enable Lazy Load</em>.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>Theme Customizer</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>In this update, we have made some changes to customizer controls and made live preview faster than before for a better user experience. Also, we have added some option settings. You can see the changes by navigating to <em>Appearance &gt; Customize</em>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Some of the important customizer option settings that are added in this update are discussed below:</p>\n\n\n\n<h4><strong>Better Way to Enable Home Page Content As in Demos.</strong></h4>\n\n\n\n<p>In previous versions of the theme, to set the home page, for example <a href=\"https://demo.themebeez.com/demos-2/cream-magazine-free/\" target=\"_blank\" aria-label=\"here (opens in a new tab)\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"rank-math-link\"><strong>here</strong></a>, the page should be created with the template option set to &#8220;Home&#8221; and then the static home page should be set via <strong>Homepage Settings</strong>. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large image-shadow\"><img src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/cream-magazine-update-2-set-homepage-option-1024x632.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-7756\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/cream-magazine-update-2-set-homepage-option-1024x632.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/cream-magazine-update-2-set-homepage-option-300x185.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/cream-magazine-update-2-set-homepage-option-768x474.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/cream-magazine-update-2-set-homepage-option.png 1213w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /><figcaption>Getting rid of selecting page attribute while creating page to set as static page</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Many users did not know or had confusion on the part of the setting template to the page. To make it simple, we&#8217;ve added an option that will load the front page as in the demos. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>To enable the option follow the instructions below:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Navigate to <em>Appearance &gt; Customize &gt; Homepage Settings</em>.</li><li>Enable option <em>Enable Homepage Content</em>.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Note: If you do not see the option, it&#8217;s because you have not set a static page for the home page.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4><strong>Manage Front Page&#8217;s Sections</strong></h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Now it&#8217;s easier to show or hide sections of the front page. Navigate to <em>Appearance &gt; Customize &gt; Front Page Customization</em> to get the options.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Note: Banner/Slider and News Ticker has been moved to Theme Customization panel.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4><strong>Sticky Menu Section and Menu Description</strong></h4>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Navigate to <em>Appearance &gt; Customize &gt; Theme Customization &gt; Header</em>.</li><li>Enable the option <em>Enable Sticky Menu Section</em> to set the menu section fixed on top while scrolling. </li><li>Enable the option <em>Enable Menu Description</em> to add a short description to the menu item. </li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>How to add menu description?</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large image-shadow\"><img src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/cream-magazine-update-2-menu-description-screen-reader-option-1024x494.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-7783\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/cream-magazine-update-2-menu-description-screen-reader-option-1024x494.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/cream-magazine-update-2-menu-description-screen-reader-option-300x145.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/cream-magazine-update-2-menu-description-screen-reader-option-768x370.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/cream-magazine-update-2-menu-description-screen-reader-option-1536x741.png 1536w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/cream-magazine-update-2-menu-description-screen-reader-option.png 1717w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /><figcaption>Enable menu description support by clicking check box from <strong>screen option </strong>toggle</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Navigate to <em>Appearance &gt; Menus</em>.</li><li>If you have already created menus, expand one of the menu items. Search for the <em>Description</em> field.</li><li>If you do not see the <em>Description</em> field, below the admin bar, click on <em>Screen Options</em>. Then check on <em>Description</em>.</li><li>Fill in the Description field and save the menu.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Menu description will look like this below in front-end of your website. </p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image image-shadow\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/cream-magazine-update-2-menu-description-1024x285.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-7757\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/cream-magazine-update-2-menu-description-1024x285.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/cream-magazine-update-2-menu-description-300x83.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/cream-magazine-update-2-menu-description-768x214.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/cream-magazine-update-2-menu-description.png 1212w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /><figcaption>Menu item description/label in navigation bar</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<h4><strong>Hide Pages on Search Results.</strong></h4>\n\n\n\n<p>In previous versions, search results contained both posts and pages. But now you can exclude pages on the search results. For this feature, follow the instructions below:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Navigate to Appearance &gt; Customize &gt; Theme Customization &gt; Search Page.</li><li>Enable option <em>Hide Pages On Search Results</em>.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h4><strong>Show Caption of Featured Image on Post/Page Single.</strong></h4>\n\n\n\n<p>We have got a few requests to add a feature to display the caption of featured image on page/page single. So in this update, we have added the feature.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Navigate to <em>Appearance &gt; Customize &gt; Theme Customization &gt; Post Single/Page Single</em>.</li><li>Enable option <em>Show Featured Image&#8217;s Caption</em>.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large image-shadow\"><img src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/cream-magazine-update-2-blog-single-featured-image-caption-1024x674.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-7758\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/cream-magazine-update-2-blog-single-featured-image-caption-1024x674.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/cream-magazine-update-2-blog-single-featured-image-caption-300x198.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/cream-magazine-update-2-blog-single-featured-image-caption-768x506.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/cream-magazine-update-2-blog-single-featured-image-caption.png 1192w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /><figcaption>Featured Image With Caption</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>But how to set image&#8217;s caption?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>When an image is uploaded in the media, click on the image to edit. Then fill the caption.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image image-shadow\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/set-image-caption-1024x436.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-7748\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/set-image-caption-1024x436.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/set-image-caption-300x128.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/set-image-caption-768x327.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/set-image-caption-1536x654.png 1536w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/set-image-caption.png 1826w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /><figcaption>Setting Image Caption</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<h4><strong>Arrange Sidebar After The Main Content in Small Devices.</strong></h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Remember, when you set sidebar position to the left, on small devices, sidebar position would not change. It would be displayed before the main content. But now you can choose to display sidebar&#8217;s after the main content. Follow the instructions below to enable this feature:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Navigate to Appearance &gt; Customize &gt; Theme Customization &gt; Sidebar.</li><li>Enable option <em>Show Sidebar After Main Content On Mobile &amp; Tablet Devices</em>.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h4><strong>Category Meta&#8217;s Color</strong></h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, you can set common color or different colors for category meta.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Navigate to <em>Appearance &gt; Customize &gt; Color Customization &gt; Category Meta Color</em>.</li><li>You&#8217;ll find the options to set colors.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image image-shadow\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/cream-magazine-update-2-category-color-option-1024x406.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-7759\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/cream-magazine-update-2-category-color-option-1024x406.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/cream-magazine-update-2-category-color-option-300x119.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/cream-magazine-update-2-category-color-option-768x304.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/cream-magazine-update-2-category-color-option.png 1204w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /><figcaption>Categories Meta With Multiple Background Colors</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<h4><strong>Link&#8217;s Color on Post/Page Single Content</strong></h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Many users enquired us to change the color of links on post/page single content. So we have added a feature to change the color of links on post/page single content. Follow the instructions below to change the link&#8217;s color.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Navigate to <em>Appearance &gt; Customize &gt; Color Customization &gt; Post/Page Single Link Color</em>.</li><li>Select the colors with <em>Content&#8217;s Link Color</em> and <em>Content&#8217;s Link Color &#8211; On Hover</em> options.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h4><strong>Typography Options</strong></h4>\n\n\n\n<p>We have added two options to set the font family of the body and headings. The options contain a set of google font families. To set the fonts, navigate to <strong>Appearance &gt; Customize &gt; Typography Customization</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-image image-shadow\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/body-typography.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-7752\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/body-typography.png 375w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/body-typography-300x178.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 375px) 100vw, 375px\" /><figcaption>Body Typography Option</figcaption></figure></div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-image image-shadow\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/headings-typography.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-7753\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/headings-typography.png 374w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/headings-typography-300x180.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 374px) 100vw, 374px\" /><figcaption>Headings Typography Option</figcaption></figure></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<h4><strong>Accessibility</strong> And Keyboard Navigation</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Accessibility and keyboard navigation is some of the requirements that WordPress has defined. So, we have updated the theme with respect to the requirement and you may find when you focus on links and form elements, you see dotted lines around the links and form elements. Also, when you hover on links, the links are underlined by default.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you want to disable the outline and underline of links, follow the instructions below:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Navigate to <em>Appearance &gt; Customize &gt; Global &gt; Links</em>.</li><li>Disable option <em>Disable Outline On Link Focus</em> to hide the dotted lines around the links.</li><li>Disable option <em>Disable Underline Link On Hover</em> to hide the underline when you hover on links. </li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h4><strong>Option&#8217;s Value</strong></h4>\n\n\n\n<p>This is an important option that you may wanna look into if you have a website in a language other than English. This option solves the issue of saving categories in widgets settings, banner/slider settings, and new ticker settings. Navigate to <em>Appearance &gt; Customize &gt; Global &gt; Option&#8217;s Value</em>. If you have a website in a language other than English, then select &#8220;ID&#8221; otherwise select &#8220;Slug&#8221; as value for <em>Save Option&#8217;s Value As</em> option.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That&#8217;s it for the important options. However, there are still some of the options which are added in this update but not discussed. To find out more, navigate to <em>Appearance &gt; Customize</em> and see for yourself.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Conclusion</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>We know that the changes that we bring onto the theme is still is insufficient. That is why, we will be working on the theme and keep updating it. We will also be adding more features and make the theme more customizable and more efficient in the upcoming days.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>There are still the features and fixes that we have not discussed above. We would like you to see them for yourself.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you are not using Cream Magazine theme yet and directly landed on this page you can download Cream Magazine from <a aria-label=\"here (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://themebeez.com/themes/cream-magazine/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"rank-math-link\"><strong>here</strong></a>. If you were using the Cream Magazine theme for long time &amp; experienced technical issues after version 2.0.0 update please feel free to let us know at our <strong><a aria-label=\"support forum (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://themebeez.com/support-forum/cream-magazine-free-theme-support/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"rank-math-link\">support forum</a></strong>. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Write us on the comments below about what you think about this update.  Here are few links that might be useful for you. </p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"button-block\">\n<a class=\"btn-general\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://themebeez.com/themes/cream-magazine/\" target=\"_blank\">Details &amp; Downloads</a>\n\n<a class=\"btn-general\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://github.com/themebeez/cream-magazine\" target=\"_blank\">ChangeLogs</a>\n\n<a class=\"btn-general\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://themebeez.com/support-forum/cream-magazine-free-theme-support/\" target=\"_blank\">Support Forum</a>\n</div>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/cream-magazine-version-2-0-0/\">Cream Magazine Version 2.0.0 (Optimized, Features &#038; Performance)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://themebeez.com/blog\">Themebeez Blog</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:61:\"https://themebeez.com/blog/cream-magazine-version-2-0-0/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"7\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:79:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:75:\"5+ Best free LMS plugins for WordPress (Learning management system plugins)\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:63:\"https://themebeez.com/blog/best-free-lms-plugins-for-wordpress/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:72:\"https://themebeez.com/blog/best-free-lms-plugins-for-wordpress/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Sun, 29 Mar 2020 06:18:45 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17:\"WordPress plugins\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Education\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3:\"LMS\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:34:\"https://themebeez.com/blog/?p=7522\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:382:\"<p>Today&#8217;s generation is all about online learning. Students learn for e-websites and it is a...</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/best-free-lms-plugins-for-wordpress/\">5+ Best free LMS plugins for WordPress (Learning management system plugins)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://themebeez.com/blog\">Themebeez Blog</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"Editorial staff\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13107:\"\n<p>Today&#8217;s generation is all about online learning. Students learn for e-websites and it is a growing educational industry. Online education and online courses are a good way to reach out to learners. That&#8217;s why we need the best free LMS plugins for WordPress. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>WordPress Learning Management System (LMS) plugins allow us to build and run e-learning websites. It makes easy to create course content &amp; lessons. manage them and to sell them. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Following are the top downloaded best free LMS plugins for WordPress (Learning Management System plugins) </h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Here I have listed the top most downloaded LMS plugins in WordPress. These plugins are great at managing course content &amp; lessons, secures your courses, tracks the progress, handles subscriptions and run quiz questions.  Following are the powerful learning management system (LMS) plugins for WordPress:   </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>LearnPress</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large theme-image\"><img src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/LearnPress-Screen_Shot-1024x474.png\" alt=\"LearnPress-Screen_Shot\" class=\"wp-image-7647\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/LearnPress-Screen_Shot-1024x474.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/LearnPress-Screen_Shot-300x139.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/LearnPress-Screen_Shot-768x356.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/LearnPress-Screen_Shot.png 1282w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>LearnPress is one of the best free LMS plugins for WordPress that helps to create a learning management system(LMS) website. It is a learning tool to create an educational course and to share the course. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Using this plugin you will be able to create online courses, manage the online courses and sell those online courses. The courses curriculum involves quizzes and lessons. You can also create online school sites, educational sites, online course sites, and other similar sites. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>It provides a bunch of free adds-ons such as LearnPress Wishlist, LearnPress Course Review, LearnPress Import/Export, LearnPress Offline Payment, LearnPress BuddyPress Integration, LearnPress Prerequisites Courses and LearnPress Fill in Blanks. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>This LearnPress LMS plugin has been translated into 16 different languages. It is made for WordPress themes. Through this plugin, you can communicate with your students. It is a user-friendly plugin. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Features of LearnPress LMS</h3>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Supports WordPress Multisites</li><li>Supports Almost all WordPress Themes</li><li>Communicate with Students(BuddyPress Support)</li><li>Provides a Bunch of Add-ons</li><li>Actively Updates and Develops</li><li>Create a Course</li><li>Manage Course</li><li>Sell Course</li><li>In 16 Different Language</li><li>Full Documentation</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"button-block\">\n<a class=\"btn-general\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/learnpress/\" target=\"_blank\">Details/Downloads LearnPress</a>\n\n<a class=\"btn-general get-hosting\" rel=\"dofollow noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/best-wordpress-hosting-compared/\" target=\"_blank\">Get Hosting</a>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<h3>LifterLMS</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large theme-image\"><img src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/LifterLMS-Screen_Shot-1024x459.png\" alt=\"LifterLMS-Screen_Shot.png\" class=\"wp-image-7648\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/LifterLMS-Screen_Shot-1024x459.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/LifterLMS-Screen_Shot-300x134.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/LifterLMS-Screen_Shot-768x344.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/LifterLMS-Screen_Shot.png 1290w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>LifterLMS is an education-based business plugin and it is also one of the best free LMS plugins for WordPress. It is built for WordPress and supports all the well-coded WordPress themes. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The main feature of this plugin is that it protects engaging online courses websites as well as training based membership websites. Plus it creates online courses and sells them online. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>This WordPress plugin supports all the popular WordPress page builders such as Beaver Builder, Elementor, Divi and more. It is the all in one solution plugin for creating educational courses and managing them. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>LifterLMS is suitable for many individuals and agencies such as freelancers, marketing agencies, publishers, education institutions, governments, enterprise companies, it departments etc. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3> Features </h3>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Education-Based Business</li><li>Create Courses</li><li>Engage With Your Students</li><li>Offer  MemberShip</li><li>Integrate With Necessary Tools</li><li>Secure and Protect Your Content</li><li>Own and Manage Your Own Platform</li><li>19 Different Languages</li><li>Support</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"button-block\">\n<a class=\"btn-general\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/lifterlms/\" target=\"_blank\">Details/Downloads LifterLMS</a>\n\n<a class=\"btn-general get-hosting\" rel=\"dofollow noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/best-wordpress-hosting-compared/\" target=\"_blank\">Get Hosting</a>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<h3>Tutor LMS</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large theme-image\"><img src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Tutor-LMS-Screen_Shot-1024x462.png\" alt=\"Tutor-LMS-Screen_Shot.png\" class=\"wp-image-7649\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Tutor-LMS-Screen_Shot-1024x462.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Tutor-LMS-Screen_Shot-300x135.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Tutor-LMS-Screen_Shot-768x347.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Tutor-LMS-Screen_Shot.png 1312w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Tutor LMS is a learning management system(LMS) plugin that helps to build e-learning website. You will be able to create an educational website, online course website and online school websites and more.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Using this plugin you will be able to create challenging quiz questions, detail reports and interactive lessons. It contents all the features that are related to online course management and its market place.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here, you can easily create an online course and sell the online course. This plugin is far practicable for creating unlimited courses and lessons, video lessons, define course duration, Q&amp;A for students with course teacher, quiz timer, quiz attempts and more. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>It is one of the best free LMS plugins for WordPress that is for creating fully functional e-learning WordPress websites. It is a lightweight  plugin and that administer, manage and monetize your e-learning website.  It is packed with lots of features.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3> Features </h3>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>9 Different Languages</li><li>Lessons &amp; Quizzes Management</li><li>Teacher Profiles and Panels</li><li>Intuitive Course Builder</li><li>Course Widget</li><li>Course Review and Rating System</li><li>Course Marketplace</li><li>Tracking Course Progress</li><li>RTL Ready</li><li>Gutenberg Compatible</li><li>Content Security</li><li>Page Builder Support</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"button-block\">\n<a class=\"btn-general\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/tutor/\" target=\"_blank\">Details/Downloads Tutor LMS</a>\n\n<a class=\"btn-general get-hosting\" rel=\"dofollow noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/best-wordpress-hosting-compared/\" target=\"_blank\">Get Hosting</a>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<h3>Sensei LMS</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large theme-image\"><img src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Sensei-LMS-Screen_Shot-1024x480.png\" alt=\"Sensei-LMS-Screen_Shot.png\" class=\"wp-image-7650\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Sensei-LMS-Screen_Shot-1024x480.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Sensei-LMS-Screen_Shot-300x141.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Sensei-LMS-Screen_Shot-768x360.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Sensei-LMS-Screen_Shot.png 1276w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Sensei LMS is one of the best free LMS plugins for WordPress that effortlessly integrates with your WordPress websites. Meaning you do not have to code. You can create an online learning website without the knowledge of code. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here you can create quizzes and lessons for your students. It strengthens students understanding and you can keep track of the progress of your students. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>This plugin has been translated into six different languages. You can easily create an e-learning website by using your prefered theme with it. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Like other Learning Management System (LMS) plugins it is heavily used for creating online courses &amp; lessons and to sell them. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3> Features </h3>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Quizzes that Acess and Reinforce</li><li>No Coding Required</li><li>Seamless WordPress Integration</li><li>Earn Passive Income</li><li>6 Different language</li><li>Create a Course</li><li>Manage Course</li><li>Sell Course</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"button-block\">\n<a class=\"btn-general\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/sensei-lms/\" target=\"_blank\">Details/Downloads Sensei LMS</a>\n\n<a class=\"btn-general get-hosting\" rel=\"dofollow noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/best-wordpress-hosting-compared/\" target=\"_blank\">Get Hosting</a>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<h3>MasterStudy LMS</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large theme-image\"><img src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MasterStudy-LMS-Screen_Shot-1024x477.png\" alt=\"MasterStudy-LMS-Screen_Shot.png\" class=\"wp-image-7651\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MasterStudy-LMS-Screen_Shot-1024x477.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MasterStudy-LMS-Screen_Shot-300x140.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MasterStudy-LMS-Screen_Shot-768x358.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MasterStudy-LMS-Screen_Shot.png 1274w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>MasterStudy LMS is one of the best free LMS plugins for WordPress. It is a powerful tool for creating online course and lesson websites. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here you can create online lessons &amp; courses content, grading quizzes, handle subscriptions, accept payments, running quizzes and more. You can even incorporate videos, images, graphs, additional attachments and slides. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is a user-friendly plugin. You can easily install and customize it.  You can set up a course with course level, skill level, time range, and the number of students. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>MasterStudy LMS plugin has a clear, clean and simple design layout that helps to create professional-looking e-learning websites. You can use this plugin with almost every kind of WordPress themes related to e-learning. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3> Features of MasterStudy LMS</h3>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Create a Course</li><li>Developing Lessons </li><li>Constructing Quizzes</li><li>Course Duration and Time Range</li><li>Clean Design </li><li>User-Friendly Interface</li><li>Manage Course</li><li>Sells Course</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"button-block\">\n<a class=\"btn-general\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/masterstudy-lms-learning-management-system/\" target=\"_blank\">Details/Downloads MasterStudy LMS</a>\n\n<a class=\"btn-general get-hosting\" rel=\"dofollow noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/best-wordpress-hosting-compared/\" target=\"_blank\">Get Hosting</a>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<h3>Conclusion </h3>\n\n\n\n<p>LMS plugins are popular nowadays. Many education institutions have started to create e-learning websites for sharing courses with students. It saves time and teachers can track the progress of students on the bases of submitted reports by students.  </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Thus it concludes the list of the top downloaded best free LMS plugins for WordPress. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>You are free to leave a comment and recommend me other learning management system plugins in the comment section below. So, that I can have your response and I will be there to reply. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Thank you for reading my post. </p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/best-free-lms-plugins-for-wordpress/\">5+ Best free LMS plugins for WordPress (Learning management system plugins)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://themebeez.com/blog\">Themebeez Blog</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:68:\"https://themebeez.com/blog/best-free-lms-plugins-for-wordpress/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\